cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use Shadow in academic work or reproducible research, please cite it as below."
title: "Shadow: Git-native behavioral diff and shadow deployment for LLM agents"
abstract: >-
  Shadow is an open-source tool for detecting, quantifying, and
  causally attributing behavioral drift in LLM-based agents. It
  provides a content-addressed trace format (.agentlog), nine
  pre-defined behavioral axes with bootstrap 95% confidence intervals,
  and LASSO-over-corners causal attribution with Meinshausen-Bühlmann
  stability selection — all runnable locally with no cloud dependency.
